<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-570-348  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 570 348.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 28 1989 v6 n34 p76(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fast document retrieval. (Law)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Compulink Management Center (product introduction).andO;Product:   LaserFiche (Disk storage device) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Legal ApplicationsInformation Storage and RetrievalProduct IntroductionDisk Storage.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Complex litigation creates demands for complex document-storage and-retrieval systems.andM;Keeping track of tens of thousands or hundreds of thousands of documents is adaunting task, especially when rapid retrieval is critical.andM;Scanners and personal computers have long been helpful in this task, but newsystems on the market show an increasing level of sophistication, couplingthe latest scanning, optical character recognition and storage technologywith the needs of legal practice.andM;One recently introduced system shown at this month's American Bar Associationannual conference was the LaserFiche document archive, search, update andretrieval system from Compulink Management Center in Torrance, Calif.andM;System configurations include input-only and output-only workstations,stand-alone I/O systems and network servers, ranging in price from $15,000 to$47,000.andM;The system scans pages at the rate of 15 seconds each and stores them in aslittle as 25K bytes on a pair of 810M-byte write once/read mostly (WORM)drives.andP;  It uses a Kurzweil engine to perform sophisticated multifont opticalcharacter recognition, so it can store full ASCII text from scanneddocuments.andM;LaserFiche uses its own high-speed search software to retrieve documents anddisplay them on a custom 19-inch 2,048-by-1,536-pixel monochrome display.andO;Output is via a 300-dot-per-inch laser printer.andM;Also exhibiting at the ABA's annual conference was CPT Corp., showing threemodels of the CPT Image File System, which range in price from $25,000 to$40,000.andM;CPT Corp., Eden Prairie, Minn.: (612-937-8000.andM;Compulink: (213) 212-LINK.andO;</TEXT></DOC>